snippet.textDisplay:
I was 7 when I saw the "movie" in theatres with my dad.
I wasn't a critic yet, but and so, I still look back on it fondly because of how much I enjoyed it at the time.
I was able to continue to watch the show, and to my delight it grew up and matured with me.
And now, 11 years after I first saw the movie. I finally get to see it end.
And as annoying as it was to wait, and painful as it was to hear it was canceled, here we are. And ultimately it was because of the wait that we get to see the show with by far the best visuals it has ever had, and likely the best musical score it has ever had.
This is the first season of clone wars I will be watching critically as well as for enjoyment, and I could not be more excited.

The fact that it is actually getting to end is surreal.
Thank you filoni for making this show happen.

snippet.textDisplay: Okay Disney, eventhough this is the final season, please make another season in non chronological order which fills in some gaps and adds some of the already previously planned arcs. This final season feels too short. Crystal Crisis on Utapau is not in this season despite it having finished story reels. Fans would probably want to see an animated version of Son of Dathomir and Dark Disciple aswell. This season does feel like a final, but not of the clone wars. More like the final of Ahsoka's story which is not bad , but we probably won't see any Grievous, Dooku or an explanation for what happened to Darth Maul after he got defeated by the Emperor. I'm glad we get this final season, but it also feels like a wasted opportunity by having only 12 episodes and leaving out so many stories.
